# Installation

## Prerequisites

- Ubuntu 20.04/22.04
- Git
- Python 3
- CMake
- Gazebo Classic 11
- MAVProxy

---

## 1. Clone ArduPilot

```bash
git clone https://github.com/ArduPilot/ardupilot.git
cd ardupilot
git submodule update --init --recursive
```

---

## 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
Tools/environment_install/install-prereqs-ubuntu.sh -y
```

Restart your terminal after installation.

---

## 3. Build ArduPilot SITL

```bash
./waf configure --board sitl
./waf copter
```

---

## 4. Clone ArduPilot Gazebo Plugin

```bash
cd ~
git clone https://github.com/ArduPilot/ardupilot_gazebo.git
```

---

## 5. Build the Gazebo Plugin

```bash
cd ~/ardupilot_gazebo
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make -j$(nproc)
```

---

## 6. Configure Environment Variables

Add the following lines to your `~/.bashrc`:

```bash
export GAZEBO_MODEL_PATH=$HOME/ardupilot_gazebo/models:$GAZEBO_MODEL_PATH
export GAZEBO_RESOURCE_PATH=$HOME/ardupilot_gazebo/worlds:$GAZEBO_RESOURCE_PATH
export GAZEBO_PLUGIN_PATH=$HOME/ardupilot_gazebo/build:$GAZEBO_PLUGIN_PATH
```

Reload the terminal:

```bash
source ~/.bashrc
```

---

## 7. Launch Gazebo

```bash
cd ~/ardupilot_gazebo
gazebo worlds/iris_arducopter_runway.world
```

---

## 8. Start ArduPilot SITL

Open a new terminal:

```bash
cd ~/ardupilot

Tools/autotest/sim_vehicle.py \
-v ArduCopter \
-f gazebo-iris \
--console \
--map
```

---

## 9. Basic Flight Commands

```text
mode GUIDED
arm throttle
takeoff 10
land
```
